note = |from H.S. days at Gould Academy I'd had this glaze mixed up for years
note = |and retried it. Very dry matt deep turquoise blue/green going to teal
note = |where thick. Beige where thin. Didn't react well to CB slip Well I
note = |finally got around to typing this thing up...^9-10 Blues Thank you
note = |one and all for all the donated recipes. I only tested 31 out of
note = |almost 100 I received. I'll continue testing and reporting as the
note = |winter DRAGS on. All the glazes were tested on #900 Miller clay which
note = |is a toasty ^10 stoneware. One side of the test tile was brushed with
note = |a thick coating of Cynthia Bringle's wet/dry white slip. Each glaze
note = |was dipped in three thicknesses on a heavily textured tile. All tiles
note = |were fired to a (hard)^9 (10 tipping)reduction firing. 1 hr. Body
note = |reduction at ^08 and 1 hr. glaze reduction at ^9 then a quick reox.
note = |before shutdown. Any time potash or Custer spar is called for, I used
note = |G-200. All ball clay is OM-4 . Many glazes I substituted 75% of the
note = |amount of Barium with Strontium. All kaolin is EPK. Remember...
note = |glazes don't travel well. Your results will probably be TOTALLY
note = |different. Please test before use. Tracy Wilson Saltbox Pottery 4
note = |Shaw Rd. Woolwich, ME 04579 phone: 207-443-5586 fax: 207-442-8922
note = |email: saltbox@ime.net web: http://www.ime.net/~dwilson/
