note = |Thank you one and all for all the donated recipes. I only tested 31
note = |out of almost 100 I received. I'll continue testing and reporting as
note = |the winter DRAGS on. All the glazes were tested on #900 Miller clay
note = |which is a toasty ^10 stoneware. One side of the test tile was
note = |brushed with a thick coating of Cynthia Bringle's wet/dry white slip.
note = |Each glaze was dipped in three thicknesses on a heavily textured
note = |tile. All tiles were fired to a (hard)^9 (10 tipping)reduction
note = |firing. 1 hr. Body reduction at ^08 and 1 hr. glaze reduction at ^9
note = |then a quick reox. before shutdown. Any time potash or Custer spar is
note = |called for, I used G-200. All ball clay is OM-4 . Many glazes I
note = |substituted 75% of the amount of Barium with Strontium. All kaolin is
note = |EPK. Remember... glazes don't travel well. Your results will probably
note = |be TOTALLY different. Please test before use. Tracy Wilson Saltbox
note = |Pottery 4 Shaw Rd. Woolwich, ME 04579 phone: 207-443-5586 fax:
note = |207-442-8922 email: saltbox@ime.net web: http://www.ime.net/~dwilson/

