note = |GREAT BLUE/RED /DARK BLUE! My experience with copper red is that what matters
note = |most is to begin reduction at cone 012 fairly heavy and then go into moderate
note = |reduction after cone 05 drops. Continue moderate to light reduction until cone 10
note = |then a brief oxidation peroid of about 10 minutes. If you over reduce it will be
note = |liver brown and under reduced will be celadon. One solution to a problem (uneven,
note = |spotty reduction and under reduced)we had was to turn down the gas and air. To
note = |slow it down and reduce at the above schedule. We were firing in an Alpine
note = |updraft with blowers and just running the same schedule as the people who fired
note = |before us. They were firing at 4 pounds pressure (natural gas) with the blowers
note = |at 70. Something like that. But we reduced the gas and the air and the firing was
note = |100% better. No more spotty reduction or unreduced pots. submitted by: John Britt
note = |e-mail: claydude@erinet.com

