note = |White RETRY My experience with copper red is that what matters most
note = |is to begin reduction at cone 012 fairly heavy and then go into
note = |moderate reduction after cone 05 drops. Continue moderate to light
note = |reduction until cone 10 then a brief oxidation peroid of about 10
note = |minutes. If you over reduce it will be liver brown and under reduced
note = |will be celadon. One solution to a problem (uneven, spotty reduction
note = |and under reduced)we had was to turn down the gas and air. To slow it
note = |down and reduce at the above schedule. We were firing in an Alpine
note = |updraft with blowers and just running the same schedule as the people
note = |who fired before us. (It was a community center). They were firing at
note = |4 pounds pressure (natural gas) with the blowers at 70. Something
note = |like that. But we reduced the gas and the air and the firing was 100%
