note = |NOTE: originally specified anhydrous Soda Ash Lowell Baker: Here are
note = |three more shino glazes for you to explore. One is probably well
note = |known, Shaner's shino, it is the one we use at Mohawk C's 'ceramics
note = |lab' stoney creek. As quoted this is a high alkali glaze (sodium and
note = |lithium) and unusually high alumina 1.6 moles (29.5% by weight). This
note = |glaze doesn't fit the pattern of C10R glazes but works if one applies
note = |it carefully. (The iron comes from the raw materials and totals 0.01
note = |moles, 0.35%) A thin singlecoat yeilds variegated organge especially
note = |on a embossed surface. If a second coat is applied, one gets a greyed
note = |white, and if the glaze is even thicker it will crawl. From: Tom Buck

