note = |GREAT BLUE/RED /DARK BLUE! My experience with copper red is that what
note = |matters most is to begin reduction at cone 012 fairly heavy and then
note = |go into moderate reduction after cone 05 drops. Continue moderate to
note = |light reduction until cone 10 then a brief oxidation peroid of about
note = |10 minutes. If you over reduce it will be liver brown and under
note = |reduced will be celadon. One solution to a problem (uneven, spotty
note = |reduction and under reduced)we had was to turn down the gas and air.
note = |To slow it down and reduce at the above schedule. We were firing in
note = |an Alpine updraft with blowers and just running the same schedule as
