note = |from Alfred/ Jim Chalkley Couldn't detect any light. blue but I
note = |remember it used to be beautiful on carved porcelain. (Jim, are you
note = |out there?) Well I finally got around to typing this thing up...^9-10
note = |Blues Thank you one and all for all the donated recipes. I only
note = |tested 31 out of almost 100 I received. I'll continue testing and
note = |reporting as the winter DRAGS on. All the glazes were tested on #900
note = |Miller clay which is a toasty ^10 stoneware. One side of the test
note = |tile was brushed with a thick coating of Cynthia Bringle's wet/dry
note = |white slip. Each glaze was dipped in three thicknesses on a heavily
note = |textured tile. All tiles were fired to a (hard)^9 (10
note = |tipping)reduction firing. 1 hr. Body reduction at ^08 and 1 hr. glaze
note = |reduction at ^9 then a quick reox. before shutdown. Any time potash
note = |or Custer spar is called for, I used G-200. All ball clay is OM-4 .
note = |Many glazes I substituted 75% of the amount of Barium with Strontium.
note = |All kaolin is EPK. Remember... glazes don't travel well. Your results
note = |will probably be TOTALLY different. Please test before use. tracy
note = |wilson <saltbox@ime.net> Tracy Wilson Saltbox Pottery 4 Shaw Rd.
note = |Woolwich, ME 04579 phone: 207-443-5586 fax: 207-442-8922 email:
